<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-58-0078 </DOCNO><TEXT>The experience of Abbott Laboratories in negotiating lower electric powerrates with electric utilities is discussed. Recommended approaches tothe utilities and a variety of rate structures are described. Finally,cogeneration as a useful negotiating tool is explained. Depending uponthe excess capacity of an electric utility, cogeneration can result inan attractive buy-back rate and an avoided cost rate for cogeneratedelectricity, or it can be a rider to the rate structure whereby the utilitywill pay your company not to run a cogeneration plant.</TEXT></DOC>